attributes.Long form description: The instructor instructs the student to disassemble the Knarrevik table. The student approaches and holds the leg of the table, grabs the allen wrench, and unscrews all the first hex socket heads on each leg portion. Then the student starts to unscrew all the second hex socket heads on each leg. After removing the hex socket heads, the student lifts the Knarrevik table to remove its top table. Next, he unscrews the two remaining hex socket heads on the first leg to disassemble them. The student flips the furniture to unscrew and disassemble the second leg. The same way he does on the third and fourth leg of the table.

attributes.Action sentence: The student unscrews the second hex socket head on the second leg.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student drops the hex socket head accidentally.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the first leg.
The student disassembles the second leg.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student drops the allen wrench accidentally.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the third leg.
The student disassembles the fourth leg and the shelf of the furniture.
